:[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#local-stack","content":"Stop the local stack when finished:"},"63":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-18","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#build-from-source","content":"Use `docker-compose-build.yml` for CI, contribution checks, and local validation of ingest service changes from this checkout:"},"64":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-19","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#build-from-source","content":"`docker-compose-build.yml` keeps the same ClickHouse, environment, ports, health checks, and migration-on-start behavior as the default stack, but replaces the GHCR ingest image with `build.context: .` and `packages/ingest-service/Dockerfile`."},"65":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-20","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"Run the ingest service as a container close to ClickHouse. Put it behind a TLS-terminating reverse proxy or load balancer. Browser applications talk to the public HTTPS ingest URL. Backend services can use the same public URL or a private network URL."},"66":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-21","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"Recommended production model:"},"67":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-22","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"one or more ingest service containers,"},"68":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-23","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"shared ClickHouse database on a supported stable or LTS ClickHouse release,"},"69":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-24","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[